## Runtime extras (`[project.optional-dependencies].runtime`)

These are installed via `pip install tac[runtime]` for GPU training/eval deploys.
The remote bootstrap scripts in `scripts/remote_*_bootstrap.sh` install this extra.

### av (PyAV)
- Version: `>=10.0`
- License: **BSD 3-Clause**
- Upstream: https://github.com/PyAV-Org/PyAV
- Copyright: Copyright (c) 2017, Mike Boers and others.
- Note: PyAV is a Python binding to FFmpeg. FFmpeg itself is licensed under
  LGPL-2.1+ (with optional GPL components); the Modal/Vast.ai/Kaggle worker
  images install the FFmpeg binary separately. FFmpeg is dynamically linked,
  not statically linked or redistributed by this project, so LGPL obligations
  are satisfied by the upstream binary distributors (BtbN FFmpeg-Builds for
  Modal; system `apt`/`brew` for local). Distributors of binary archives that
  bundle FFmpeg must comply separately.

