## Modal-only worker image deps (`experiments/modal_train_lane.py:60-83`)

The Modal worker image pip-installs an additional set on top of the project deps,
listed here for completeness. These are functionally a subset/superset of the
`[runtime]` extra plus DALI for GPU video decode:

| Package | License | Upstream |
|---------|---------|----------|
| torchvision | BSD 3-Clause | https://github.com/pytorch/vision |
| tqdm | MIT + MPL-2.0 (dual) | https://github.com/tqdm/tqdm |
| Pillow | HPND | https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow |
| scipy | BSD 3-Clause | https://github.com/scipy/scipy |
| nvidia-dali-cuda120 | Apache-2.0 | https://github.com/NVIDIA/DALI |

## Pinned upstream snapshot

This repository bundles a pinned snapshot of the upstream Comma Video Compression
Challenge harness under `upstream/`. The snapshot is governed by its own license
as published by comma.ai; see `upstream/LICENSE` (or, if absent, the upstream
repository at https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge).
Per CLAUDE.md's "Non-Negotiable Upstream Rule" this snapshot is not modified.

## Research inspirations / referenced projects

This pack does not vendor third-party source code from the projects below, but it
is designed to interoperate with them or references them in documentation:

- `commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge` — upstream challenge repo.
- `Yeachan-Heo/oh-my-codex` and related OMX tooling — referenced for the
  Ralph-style Codex workflow.
- `iannuttall/ralph` — referenced as a file-based loop model and optional CLI
  lane.
- `karpathy/autoresearch` — conceptual inspiration for constrained experiment
  loops.
- DSPy / GEPA — conceptual inspiration for evolving prompts and other
  text-shaped artifacts.
- `NousResearch/hermes-agent-self-evolution` — conceptual inspiration for
  persistent optimization loops.
- Modular Mojo documentation — referenced for the optional experimental Mojo
  lane.

Please review the licenses and terms of any third-party code you clone or install
separately.

## How to review or update this file

When `pyproject.toml` dependencies change, this file MUST be updated in the same
commit batch. The canonical procedure:

1. Compare the `pyproject.toml` dependency lists against the entries below.
2. For any new package, look up its license via `pip show <pkg>` or its
   upstream repository.
3. If the license is anything other than MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD-2/3-Clause /
   HPND / ISC / PSF / MPL-2.0 (dev only) / BSL-1.0, surface as a BLOCKER for
   operator review before adding the dep.
4. Re-run `python tools/check_third_party_notices.py` (if it exists) to verify
   the lock matches.
